Step1
Install Docker Desktop

Step2
Enable Kubernetes
1.Open the Docker Dashboard: Launch the Docker Desktop application on your system.
2.Navigate to Settings: Click the gear icon (Settings or Preferences) in the top-right or sidebar of the Docker Dashboard.
3.Select the Kubernetes Tab: In the Settings menu, find and select the Kubernetes tab.
4.Enable Kubernetes: Check the box labeled Enable Kubernetes.
5.Apply & Restart: Click the Apply & Restart button at the bottom of the settings window. Docker Desktop will then download the necessary Kubernetes components and start a single-node cluster. This may take a few minutes the first time

